<item>
            <title>[OPENJPA-2035] Add the ability to cache data on a remote process without needing domain classes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OPENJPA-2035</link>
                <project id="12310351" key="OPENJPA">OpenJPA</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have a remote cache running and I don&apos;t want to have to add my domain classes to the remote cache&apos;s classpath. With this JIRA I&apos;m going to lift this restriction.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently OpenJPAId and PCDataImpl have hard references to the domain Class files that they are operating over. We could change these references to transient and keep a hold of the stringified class names to reload the class if necessary. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
